<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><law><structure><unit label="title" identifier="XXIX" order_by="29">COMMERCE AND TRADE</unit><unit label="chapter" identifier="" order_by=""></unit></structure><section_number>355.2-303</section_number><catch_line>Allocation or division of risks. </catch_line><order_by>2-303</order_by><text>Where this article allocates a risk or a burden as between the parties "unless otherwise agreed," the agreement may not only shift the allocation but may also divide the risk or burden. </text><history>Created 1958 Ky. Acts ch. 77, sec. 2-303, effective July 1, 1960. </history><metadata><effective>July 1, 1960 </effective><pdf-author>ganesan_m</pdf-author><pdf-creation-date>2015-07-02</pdf-creation-date><pdf-download-date>2016-03-18 12:15:46</pdf-download-date><original-link>http://www.lrc.ky.gov/statutes/statute.aspx?id=33263</original-link></metadata><tags><tag>computer-parsed</tag><tag>unverified</tag></tags></law>